latestPosts.caption:
A film that starts with a suicide attempt… and turns into a wild, darkly funny ride where being left-handed becomes a full-blown curse. Edagaiye Apaghatakke Karana is bold, inventive, and rooted deeply in Kannada culture. New-age storytelling, fresh talent, and clever filmmaking, all packed into one unique experience. Don’t wait for OTT. Watch it in theatres. Support original Kannada cinema. 

Full review also on my YouTube channel…
